Class FluidBase

java.lang.Object
io.github.noeppi_noeppi.libx.base.FluidBase
All Implemented Interfaces:
Registerable, net.minecraft.world.level.ItemLike
public class FluidBase extends Object implements Registerable, net.minecraft.world.level.ItemLike
A Registerable that registers a fluid, a flowing fluid, a liquid block and a bucket item.

    • FluidBase

      public FluidBase​(ModX mod, Function<net.minecraftforge.fluids.ForgeFlowingFluid.Properties,​net.minecraftforge.fluids.ForgeFlowingFluid.Source> sourceFactory, Function<net.minecraftforge.fluids.ForgeFlowingFluid.Properties,​net.minecraftforge.fluids.ForgeFlowingFluid.Flowing> flowingFactory, UnaryOperator<net.minecraftforge.fluids.FluidAttributes.Builder> attributes, net.minecraft.world.level.block.state.BlockBehaviour.Properties blockProperties, net.minecraft.world.item.Item.Properties itemProperties)
      Creates a new instance of FluidBase
      Parameters:
      sourceFactory - A factory to create a still fluid from the fluids properties. In most cases this will just be a constructor reference.
      flowingFactory - A factory to create a flowing fluid from the fluids properties. In most cases this will just be a constructor reference.
      attributes - A function to modify the attribute builder to alter the fluids attributes
      blockProperties - The properties for the fluids block
      itemProperties - The properties for the bucket item

    • getNamedAdditionalRegisters

      public Map<String,​Object> getNamedAdditionalRegisters​(net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation id)
      Description copied from interface: Registerable
      Gets additional items that should be registered. Those may be Registerable as well. These objects will be registered with the id of this registerable appended by their key in the map. This allows to register multiple thing to the same registry.
      Specified by:
      getNamedAdditionalRegisters in interface Registerable
